# Agent workflow

## Branch naming

```
<type>/<short-description>
```

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `chore`, `test`

Examples:
- `feat/user-auth`
- `fix/null-pointer-on-empty-input`
- `docs/update-api-reference`

Always branch from `main`. Keep branches short-lived.

## Issue and PR workflow

{% if platform in ('forgejo', 'both') %}
### Forgejo (`fj`)

```bash
# List open issues
fj issue list

# Create an issue
fj issue create --title "..." --body "..."

# Create a PR from current branch
fj pr create --title "..." --body "..." --base main

# List open PRs
fj pr list

# Merge a PR (after CI passes)
fj pr merge <number> --squash

# Create a release tag (triggers CD)
fj release create v1.2.3 --title "v1.2.3" --notes "..."
```
{% endif %}
{% if platform in ('github', 'both') %}
### GitHub (`gh`)

```bash
# List open issues
gh issue list

# Create an issue
gh issue create --title "..." --body "..."

# Create a PR from current branch
gh pr create --title "..." --body "..." --base main

# List open PRs
gh pr list

# Merge a PR (after CI passes)
gh pr merge <number> --squash

# Create a release tag (triggers CD)
gh release create v1.2.3 --title "v1.2.3" --notes "..."
```
{% endif %}

## Label conventions

| Label | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| `bug` | Something is broken |
| `feature` | New capability |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `refactor` | Internal change, no behaviour change |
| `breaking` | Breaks backwards compatibility |
| `blocked` | Waiting on external dependency |

## PR checklist

Before opening a PR:

1. All quality gates pass locally (see [quality-gates.md](quality-gates.md))
2. PR description explains *why*, not just *what*
3. Breaking changes are labelled `breaking` and noted in the PR body
4. Any new architectural decisions are recorded in `docs/adr/`

## Releases

Releases are triggered by pushing a version tag:

```bash
git tag v1.2.3
git push origin v1.2.3
```

This triggers the CD workflow{% if has_api %} which builds and pushes the Docker image{% endif %}.

Use [semver](https://semver.org/): `vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`.
